project3.lex
Class File

java.lang.Object
  project3.lex.File

public class File
extends java.lang.Object

Conceptually we can think of a File as a sequence, s, of n characters where n >= 1. s[0] is the 'front' character of the File. s[|s|-1] = File.EOF.

A File also contains the current line number.

Domain Definition:

      s : Sequence<Character>
      lineNumber : int 
 Instance Invariant:
     |s| >= 1 AND s[|s|-1] = File.EOF

File

public File(java.lang.String fileName)
Creates a new File that reads from the file with the name "fileName". If no such file exists, it reads from standard input.

Precondition: none
Postcondition: File with fileName exists ⇒ s = file with file name "fileName" + File.EOF
File with fileName does not exist ⇒ s = System.in + File.EOF

popFront

public void popFront()
If |s| > 1 popFront removes the front character or s[0] from s, otherwise it does nothing.

Precondition: none
